item.title: Report E-2024070779
item.description:
Report E-2024070779

Identified by scraper @ 2024-08-14T15:13:37+00:00

  • Incident Date: 2024-07-10
  • City: Russell
  • State: KY
  • Report Type: A hazardous material incident
  • Mode Of Transportation: Rail
  • Carrier/Reporter: CSX TRANSPORTATION, INC.
  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Total Amount Of Damages: 15000
  • Serious Incident Ind: No
  • Description: On 07/10/2024, at 0541hrs., personnel in the CSXT Russell Yard discovered SIRX23534, a loaded tank car of Elevated Temperature, Liquid N.O.S. (Asphalt), leaking from under the jacket at the B-end brake support bracket onto the break assembly. The car was isolated and the shipper, Marathon Petroleum, was notified via CHEMTREC (Report #2024-0710-0049). Quick Response, a CSXT emergency response contractor, was dispatched to the scene and found product had leaked from under the jacket onto the brake assembly support but turned viscous as it cooled down and was malleable but solid. Subsequent investigation determined that the product released from the car due to a crack in the tank shell. The car was held out of transportation pending further investigation and observation by the owner and FRA, and pending a procedure to safely unload the car.

item.title: Report X-2024080599
item.description:
Report X-2024080599

Identified by scraper @ 2024-08-12T15:14:41+00:00

  • Incident Date: 2024-07-31
  • City: LOUISVILLE
  • State: KY
  • Report Type: A hazardous material incident
  • Mode Of Transportation: Air
  • Carrier/Reporter: UNITED PARCEL SERVICE CO.
  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Total Amount Of Damages: 0
  • Serious Incident Ind: No
  • Description: TWO AIR DANGEROUS GOODS PACKAGES SHIPPING WITH AN IATA DECLARATION, HAZMAT LABELS AND MARKS WERE FOUND LEAKING AT THE UPS WORLDPORT FACILITY IN LOUISVILLE, KENTUCKY. THE SHIPMENT HAD PASSED AN ACCEPTANCE AUDIT AT THE ORIGIN FACILITY, FLOWN RNO TO SDF PRIOR TO THE INCIDENT DISCOVERY IN LOUISVILLE, KENTUCKY. EACH PACKAGE CONTAINS TWO X 2.5 GALLON CONTAINERS OF VAPONA CONCENTRATE INSECTICIDE. THE ADDITIONAL TRACKING NUMBER ALSO LEAKING IN THE SHIPMENT IS 1Z0V044X0118441037. INITIAL REVIEW OF THE CONTENTS REVEALS EACH PACKAGE HAD ONE CONTAINER THAT LEAKED APPROXIMATELY ONE LITER FROM WHAT APPEARS TO BE A LOOSE CLOSURE. BOTH PACKAGES ARE ON HOLD PENDING POSSIBLE FAA INSPECTION.
